# Lo Gandey — Project Memory

**Product:** Lo Gandey — proprietary smart mirror platform for the Maldives (commercial business).
**Owner:** Lo Gandey | **Contact:** adhuhamlayaal55@gmail.com
**Branding:** Use "Lo Gandey" only. No upstream names, GitHub links, or contributor references in user-facing materials.

## Architecture (dual process)

- **Node server** (`js/app.js`, `js/server.js`): config, Express :8080, Socket.IO, optional `node_helper.js`
- **Browser/Electron client** (`js/main.js`, `js/loader.js`, `js/module.js`): UI modules, `GET /config`
- Config loads **only at server restart**

## Key paths

- `config/config.js` — active config (gitignored)
- `config/config.js.sample` — Maldives template (committed)
- `defaultmodules/` — built-in modules | `modules/` — custom modules
- `updatenotification` module **removed** from default config (no git/update checks)

## Maldives defaults (Malé)

- `locale`: `en-MV` | `timezone`: `Indian/Maldives` | `lat/lon`: `4.1755`, `73.5093`
- Weather: Open-Meteo | Calendar: Google MV holidays ICS | News: TNN local RSS

## Run commands

- Dev: `npm run server` → localhost:8080 | Pi: `node --run start:x11` | Windows: `npm run start:windows`
- Install: `node --run install-mm` | Validate: `npm run config:check` | Node 22+

## Deployment

- Raspberry Pi 4/5, Pi OS 64-bit desktop, pm2/systemd auto-start, kiosk mode
- Off-grid standalone — no GitHub dependency in product UX

## Business

Turnkey mirrors, software licenses, custom modules. README is the sales page — email-only contact, no public repo links.
